Deployment in kubernetes
========================
A Deployment controller is a kubernetes workload.
Deployment is used to manage stateless application.


apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: orderservice
  labels:
    app: orderservice
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: orderservice
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: orderservice
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: orderservice
        image: your-dockerhub-username/orderservice:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        readinessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /health
            port: 8080
          initialDelaySeconds: 10
          periodSeconds: 5
        env:
        - name: APP_ENV
          value: "production"
        - name: LOG_LEVEL
          value: "info"

========================================================================
Max Surge
==========
What is max surge?
Maximum number of pods which can be created over the desired number of pods is called max surge.
if the maxsurge is 30% than the total number of pods will be 130% of the desired pods.


Rolling update deployment
=========================
Deployment update pods in rolling update fashion.
gradually scale down the old ReplicaSets and scale up the new one

Max Unavailable
================
This can be a percentage of the maximum number of pods.


Maximum unavailabe
===================
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
 name: nginx-deployment
 labels:
   app: nginx
spec:
 replicas: 3
 selector:
   matchLabels:
     app: nginx
 template:
   metadata:
     labels:
       app: nginx
   spec:
     containers:
     - name: nginx
       image: nginx:1.14.2
       ports:
       - containerPort: 80
 strategy:
   type: RollingUpdate
   rollingUpdate:
     maxSurge: 1
     maxUnavailable: 1


